<Paragraph FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="14">This sample illustrates the steps as in the User Guide to add OlapChart in an application.</Paragraph>
<Paragraph FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="15" FontWeight="Bold">Step 1:</Paragraph>
<Paragraph FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="14">Create a new WPF application. From the Visual Studio toolbox, drag and drop OlapChart under Syncfusion BI WPF section. It will automatically add the required referenced assemblies. </Paragraph>

<Paragraph FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="15" FontWeight="Bold">Step 2:</Paragraph>
<Paragraph FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="14">Right-click the OlapChart in Visual Studio designer region. Then navigate to Configure data source -> Create/Edit data source… option in the context menu.</Paragraph>
<Paragraph TextAlignment="Center"><Image Source="Images/VS_Demo_Step_1.png" Stretch="None" /></Paragraph>

<Paragraph FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="15" FontWeight="Bold">Step 3:</Paragraph>
<Paragraph FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="14">From the Data Source Property wizard, select the connection type.</Paragraph>
<List Margin="10,0,0,0">
<ListItem><Paragraph FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="14">To connect using server name and database name, then choose the first option. You can also provide credentials to login by expanding the Credentials expander.</Paragraph><Paragraph /></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="14">To connect to SSAS by providing an existing connection string, then choose the second option. </Paragraph><Paragraph /></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="14">To test the connection, click Test Connection button that is displayed on the bottom-left corner of the window. </Paragraph><Paragraph /></ListItem>
</List>
<Paragraph TextAlignment="Center"><Image Source="Images/VS_Demo_Step_2.png" Stretch="None" /></Paragraph>
<List Margin="10,0,0,0">
<ListItem><Paragraph FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="14"> Click Next button to proceed.</Paragraph><Paragraph /></ListItem>
</List>

<Paragraph FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="15" FontWeight="Bold">Step 4:</Paragraph>
<Paragraph FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="14">MDX query text box in the summary page will be empty, when you create a query for the first time. When you edit an already existing query it displays the current query in the text box. </Paragraph>
<List Margin="10,0,0,0">
<ListItem><Paragraph FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="14">For creating or editing a query, click the Create/Edit link label, that is displayed on the top-right side of the MDX query textbox. This opens the Query Designer dialog.</Paragraph><Paragraph /></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="14">When you edit an existing query, it displays the required dimensions in the specific axis of the Query Designer and the preview of that query is displayed in a Chart control.</Paragraph><Paragraph /></ListItem>
</List>
<Paragraph TextAlignment="Center"><Image Source="Images/VS_Demo_Step_3.png" Stretch="None" /></Paragraph>

<Paragraph FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="15" FontWeight="Bold">Step 5:</Paragraph>
<Paragraph FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="14">Drag and drop dimensions to form a new query.</Paragraph>
<Paragraph TextAlignment="Center"><Image Source="Images/VS_Demo_Step_4.png" Stretch="None" /></Paragraph>
<Paragraph FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="14">Then, click OK, to save the query or click Cancel, to revert the changes made during this session.</Paragraph>

<Paragraph FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="15" FontWeight="Bold">Step 6:</Paragraph>
<Paragraph FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="14">The summary page of the Data Source Properties displays the resultant MDX query.</Paragraph>
<Paragraph TextAlignment="Center"><Image Source="Images/VS_Demo_Step_5.png" Stretch="None" /></Paragraph>

<Paragraph FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="15" FontWeight="Bold">Step 7:</Paragraph>
<Paragraph FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="14">Finally, press Finish button to load the designer settings into XAML view.</Paragraph>
<Paragraph TextAlignment="Center"><Image Source="Images/VS_Demo_Step_6.png" Stretch="None" /></Paragraph>

<Paragraph TextAlignment="Center"><Image Source="Images/OlapChartConfiguration.png" Stretch="None" /></Paragraph></Section>
